  "response_text": "The commercial opens on a flat chocolate-brown background with the word “SOURDOUGH” in large, thick, white, rounded letters across the upper half. Along the bottom edge, the golden, rough-textured top of toasted bread rises into view, its browned crust and crumbly surface filling more of the screen until it partly covers the lettering behind it.\n\nA fully assembled burger then appears centered against the same brown background. It is stacked between two round, toasted sourdough buns with visible grill-like browning on the top. Inside are two charred beef patties, melted yellow cheese, strips of glossy red-brown bacon, and pale sauce tucked under the top bun. The burger sits alone, neatly lit to emphasize the layers and textures.\n\nThe view changes to an extreme close-up of toasted bread texture, golden and porous, with the word “TOASTY” repeated vertically in dark brown block letters. The letters fill the center while the toasted surface forms the entire background, reinforcing the bread’s crisp look.\n\nSeveral slices of sourdough toast then slide and stack in a row on a clean white surface. A front slice faces forward like a sign. Dark brown branding appears directly on the bread: first the Burger King logo and the word “SOURDOUGH,” then the full “BURGER KING SOURDOUGH KING” mark. Crumbs are scattered beneath the slices, and more toast slices stand behind it in soft focus.\n\nThe scene cuts to beef patties cooking on a metal grill. Several round patties are spread across the grates, with dark sear marks and glistening surfaces. Orange flames flare up between the bars beneath them, emphasizing flame-grilling.\n\nA patterned arrangement of partially assembled sandwiches appears on a white background. Multiple bottom buns hold beef patties, melted cheese, and bacon in a repeated grid-like layout. Some patties have strong grill marks; some sandwiches are open-faced, while others have round sourdough tops added, showing different stages of assembly.\n\nA close-up isolates a patty with melted yellow cheese and bacon against the brown background, overlaid with the large white word “SIZZLING.” Bacon strips curve and shine over the cheese and patty, filling the space behind the text.\n\nThe burger is then shown in an extreme close-up from the side. The words “OOEY” and “GOOEY” appear in big white letters over the sandwich as melted cheese stretches between two layers of beef. The cheese pulls into thin strands and glossy ribbons, with bacon and sauce visible above and toasted bun edges above and below.\n\nAnother tight side view lingers on the sandwich layers: two charred patties, bright melted cheese dripping over the edges, curled bacon strips, red sauce or ketchup-like glossy spots, pale sauce under the top bun, and the toasted sourdough bun pressing the stack together.\n\nThe product presentation shifts to a red serving tray set against the same brown background. A large Sourdough King sits in the center, with a smaller sandwich partly visible to the left. A tall cup of Dr Pepper stands behind the main burger on the right, filled with dark soda and ice, with a foamy top and the white Dr Pepper logo on the cup. Large white text above the food reads “SOURDOUGH KING.” Tiny legal text appears near the bottom edge of the tray area.\n\nThe tray slides left as the background splits, introducing a bright yellow panel on the right. The Sourdough King and Dr Pepper move out of prominence while a new display of breakfast sandwiches enters on a dark tray. The text resolves into “SOURDOUGH BREAKFAST KING” in large white and dark brown letters on the yellow background. Three breakfast-style sourdough sandwiches are arranged across the tray, with round toasted sourdough buns and visible layers such as folded egg, melted yellow cheese, sausage patties, bacon, and ham-like slices. Small fine print remains along the bottom, and a partial “YOUR” is visible near the tray edge.",
